Comment: 0,0:01:45.11,0:01:48.60,Titles,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.6}The Argentum Archipelago
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.40,0:02:26.37,Regular,,0,0,0,,Our Archipelago has the best science and technology on Daikuuriku.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.95,0:02:31.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,However, we have been unable to develop an airship that can fly above the clouds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.58,0:02:36.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,A single lightning strike would incinerate one in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.42,0:02:43.74,Regular,,0,0,0,,Despite the risk, we have no choice but to fly… far across the raging sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.70,0:03:10.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Holy Land is a quiet and beautiful country that hides a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.38,0:03:16.80,Regular,,0,0,0,,Our country has tried repeatedly to invade theirs to learn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.80,0:03:19.67,Regular,,0,0,0,,But every time we’ve tried,\Nthey’ve stopped us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.81,0:03:39.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,This is the Holy Land’s\Nsecret: demons. Simoun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.90,0:03:45.15,Regular,,0,0,0,,Nothing else on Daikuuriku\Ncan fly that freely in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.32,0:03:50.29,Titles,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.6}Fallen Wings
Comment: 0,0:03:50.62,0:03:53.30,Titles,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.6}The Holy Land of Simulacrum
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.40,0:04:21.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,It’s only a routine deterrence patrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.56,0:04:25.66,Regular,,0,0,0,,But everyone in the government is here \Nfor an inspection, so we’re showing off a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.17,0:04:46.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.51,0:04:48.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,You should address her\Nas “Sibylla Aurea!”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.71,0:04:51.08,Regular,,0,0,0,,You can almost see\Nthe golden glow around her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.24,0:05:07.99,Regular,,0,0,0,,Was you father well, Neviril?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.99,0:05:09.99,Regular,,0,0,0,,Amuria, you’re terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.57,0:05:52.33,Regular,,0,0,0,,There are several hundred\NRi Maajon shapes,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.33,0:05:55.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,and we can combine them\Nin an infinite number of ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.01,0:05:59.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,Many of the meanings\Nhave been lost over the years,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.63,0:06:03.67,Regular,,0,0,0,,but the Simoun sibyllae are constantly working to rediscover them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.00,0:06:08.57,Regular,,0,0,0,,Your daughter’s flying\Nis every bit as good as I’ve heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.09,0:06:12.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,Now that she’s come of age,\NI can finally breathe a sigh of relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.89,0:06:18.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,She has become the best Simoun sibylla,\Nhas she not? The one they call “Sibylla Aurea?”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.24,0:06:21.36,Regular,,0,0,0,,No matter how magnificently\Na prayer is offered,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.36,0:06:25.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,using it in war can\Nonly hurt our traditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.88,0:06:27.20,Regular,,0,0,0,,Your Eminence…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.20,0:06:31.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,Prayers are meant to be offerings. To use them for {\i1}war{\i0}, of all things…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.41,0:06:36.75,Regular,,0,0,0,,By sending the Simoun to patrol the borders,\Nwe can demonstrate the power of Tempus Spatium,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.75,0:06:41.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,and convince these insolent invaders to withdraw peacefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.58,0:06:45.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,Would that not be in accordance\Nwith the divine will?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.01,0:07:01.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,My father specifically asked for Chor Tempest to fly today’s patrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.85,0:07:04.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,He wanted to put on\Na good show for the VIPs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.52,0:07:08.36,Regular,,0,0,0,,Well, Chor Tempest is\Nthe best choir, after all…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.36,0:07:13.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,Amuria, flying the Simoun\Nisn’t about being the “best.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.23,0:07:14.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.32,0:07:19.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,When we fly, it’s to offer prayers,\Nnot for our own glory.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.25,0:07:23.33,Regular,,0,0,0,,We try to create a perfect Ri Maajon shape to offer to Tempus Spatium.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.23,0:07:27.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,We have to get stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.26,0:07:30.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,A lot stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.38,0:07:34.01,Regular,,0,0,0,,Stronger? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.89,0:07:43.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril! Can you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.99,0:07:53.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that…?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.14,0:08:23.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,This is Neviril, from Chor Tempest. Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.52,0:08:26.17,Regular,,0,0,0,,Shot down?\NWhose Simoun was shot down?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.07,0:08:29.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,They {\i1}all{\i0} were!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.73,0:08:32.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,Chor Caput has been wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.36,0:08:37.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,We’re the only ones left.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.49,0:08:43.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hurry! You must send word to Guragief-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.21,0:08:46.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Aurea, please be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.65,0:09:13.68,Regular,,0,0,0,,I thought it was impossible for a Simoun to be shot down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.68,0:09:15.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,Calm down, Neviril.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.78,0:09:23.45,Regular,,0,0,0,,We knew a day like this would come eventually, that we’d have to take the Simoun into battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.29,0:09:27.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,No, Amuria, Simoun are\Nthe chariots of the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.69,0:09:33.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,No man-made aircraft can possibly outperform these heavenly craft!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.46,0:09:38.80,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s why, when the enemy sees a Simoun, they’ll run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.80,0:09:40.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,When they see us, they’ll run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.05,0:09:42.10,Regular,,0,0,0,,Milady?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.57,0:09:45.31,Regular,,0,0,0,,Huh? Did I say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.73,0:09:47.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,Are we going to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.19,0:09:51.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh well, if I’m with you,\NPara-sama, I won’t mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.11,0:09:54.99,Regular,,0,0,0,,I have better things to do than die.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.61,0:09:57.57,Regular,,0,0,0,,Do you mean Neviril?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.90,0:10:00.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,Did she give you permission\Nto omit her title, Kaimu?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.12,0:10:03.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh, so {\i1}you’re{\i0} the one\NI need permission from?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.54,0:10:05.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,I wonder what the enemy’s like.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.25,0:10:08.75,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Archipelago use those\Nfloaty airships, don’t they?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.75,0:10:10.80,Regular,,0,0,0,,There must be some mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.80,0:10:12.90,Regular,,0,0,0,,Everyone knows that\Na Simoun can’t be shot down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.25,0:10:16.95,Regular,,0,0,0,,All we have to do is fly around and the enemy flees in terror…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.92,0:10:19.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,…from these beautiful butterflies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.72,0:10:23.28,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril, let’s try\Nthe Emerald Ri Maajon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.28,0:10:27.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,That again? That’s one of the old\N Ri Maajons that hasn’t been analyzed!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.35,0:10:32.62,Regular,,0,0,0,,According to legend, the sibyllae who successfully completed the Emerald Ri Maajon
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.62,0:10:35.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,were taken to serve at the right hand of Tempus Spatium.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.73,0:10:38.90,Regular,,0,0,0,,If we succeed at it, we can too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.26,0:10:42.80,Regular,,0,0,0,,Don’t be so impatient!\NLet’s not worry about that for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.33,0:10:44.77,Regular,,0,0,0,,But I want us to get stronger!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.91,0:10:50.10,Regular,,0,0,0,,We’ve reached the border.\NI’m taking us down.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.40,0:11:18.01,Regular,,0,0,0,,Simoun are the chariots of the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.01,0:11:22.09,Regular,,0,0,0,,They certainly perform a lot better than anything we can build.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.90,0:11:29.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,If we could learn their secret,\Nour country’s fortunes would improve.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.56,0:11:49.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,Falcon Ri Maajon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.33,0:12:13.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,They invaded our country,\Nand they’re not leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.21,0:12:20.76,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s just normal flight.\NIt’s not like the Simoun at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.17,0:12:26.14,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Simoun draw patterns in the sky with the shining trails they leave in their wake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.85,0:12:28.68,Regular,,0,0,0,,They call it “Ri Maajon.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.47,0:12:33.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,No one knows why\Nit holds such power.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.39,0:12:40.05,Regular,,0,0,0,,If we could learn the secret, it would greatly advance our country’s technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.86,0:12:45.42,Regular,,0,0,0,,But the Holy Land has kept the secrets of the Simoun closely guarded for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.42,0:12:49.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,It is said that those who\Ntry to learn these secrets
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.83,0:12:53.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,will be cast into hell\Nby the Simoun themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.54,0:12:59.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,But what of it? The Simoun are just machines,\Nand there’s no such place as hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.68,0:13:08.05,Regular,,0,0,0,,There are so many of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.68,0:13:12.84,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Simoun aren’t “the chariots of the gods.” They’re just machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.84,0:13:14.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,Therefore, they can be shot down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.23,0:13:15.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,We can bring them down!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.81,0:13:19.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,Someday the secret of the\NRi Maajon will be revealed,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.06,0:13:24.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,and the Holy Land’s monopoly of the Simoun technology will come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.99,0:13:28.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oh, who cares how many there are?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.00,0:13:31.20,Regular,,0,0,0,,We’ll get rid of them all!\NShark Ri Maajon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.92,0:13:45.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,Iron Ri Maajon, all six of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.63,0:13:46.84,Regular,,0,0,0,,Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.44,0:14:02.15,Regular,,0,0,0,,They’re erasing our trails!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.57,0:14:03.86,Regular,,0,0,0,,How can they do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.25,0:14:07.97,Regular,,0,0,0,,If they can’t draw the pattern with their trails,\Nthe Simoun can’t perform a Ri Maajon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.33,0:14:23.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,We have to try the Emerald Ri Maajon, Neviril! A miracle is sure to happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.88,0:14:26.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,No, Amuria. We don’t\Nknow what will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.67,0:14:29.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,I want to get stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.23,0:14:31.14,Regular,,0,0,0,,We need to get stronger, Neviril!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.54,0:14:33.33,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don’t want things to be like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.33,0:14:35.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,Look at all these people\Ntrying to interfere with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.71,0:14:38.19,Regular,,0,0,0,,They’re trying to take\Nour wings from us!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.19,0:14:40.65,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s why we have to fight them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.73,0:14:45.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,Amuria!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.36,0:14:48.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s why we need to get stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.04,0:14:49.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,You understand, don’t you, Neviril?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.36,0:14:53.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,We can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.55,0:15:11.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,Let’s go… to the place\Nwhere we can be free.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.13,0:15:54.55,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril! We’re going to be much stronger!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.55,0:15:55.60,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.81,0:16:06.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,She was so beautiful…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.15,0:16:10.36,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril, don’t look! If you see their eyes,\N you won’t be able to kill them!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.11,0:16:15.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.58,0:16:21.45,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Emerald Ri Maajon… failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.29,0:16:23.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,What is {\i1}that{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.60,0:16:40.89,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.40,0:16:44.60,Regular,,0,0,0,,It’s the wrath of Tempus Spatium!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.02,0:16:47.79,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Simoun are just machines!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.31,0:16:49.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,They’re not “the chariots of the gods!”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.42,0:16:54.13,Regular,,0,0,0,,Our country {\i1}will{\i0} learn\Nthese demons’ secrets!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.57,0:17:00.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,But… what if… they really are…?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.13,0:17:52.17,Regular,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.61,0:18:21.74,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Sibylla Aurea is tired.\NI’ll listen to what you have to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.74,0:18:23.27,Regular,,0,0,0,,Paraietta-sama…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.33,0:18:26.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,Um, we…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.54,0:18:28.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,You want to leave the ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.00,0:18:31.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.54,0:18:36.11,Regular,,0,0,0,,We’re thinking of going to the Spring to meet with Onashia.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.71,0:18:39.01,Regular,,0,0,0,,If you go to the Spring,\Nyou can no longer be a sibylla.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.52,0:18:42.11,Regular,,0,0,0,,You’ll never be able to\Ntouch a Simoun again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.11,0:18:42.97,Regular,,0,0,0,,Are you okay with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.97,0:18:44.13,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.13,0:18:46.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m planning to become a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.47,0:18:50.01,Regular,,0,0,0,,I want to be as gallant\Nas you, Paraietta-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.01,0:18:53.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,Your wish for the Spring isn’t something to be shared with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.12,0:18:53.94,Regular,,0,0,0,,Go on, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.91,0:19:09.29,Regular,,0,0,0,,Are you going to sit here and watch her door all day, senpai?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.50,0:19:14.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,There’s nothing I can do\N to heal that sibylla’s pain…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.30,0:19:18.20,Regular,,0,0,0,,…except to grieve alongside her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.52,0:19:32.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,A cadet?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.65,0:19:36.02,Regular,,0,0,0,,This is the sibyllae’s area. Get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.19,0:19:41.68,Regular,,0,0,0,,Are the priestesses feeling any better?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.28,0:19:47.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,They say that when the moon is covered by clouds, the stars are, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.99,0:19:52.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril lost her beloved pair.\NIt’s to be expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.92,0:19:56.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,Three sibyllae from\NChor Tempest died in the battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.98,0:19:59.67,Regular,,0,0,0,,and more are leaving\Nto go to the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.67,0:20:02.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,They’re no longer\Nthe elite, are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.54,0:20:03.84,Regular,,0,0,0,,Dux!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.34,0:20:08.10,Regular,,0,0,0,,What’s wrong, Sibylla Floe, Sibylla Limone?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.10,0:20:11.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,The thing is, this kid— wait,\Nshe’s a sibylla? But…!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.85,0:20:16.06,Regular,,0,0,0,,She may be young, but she has special permission to join Chor Tempest.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.28,0:20:25.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,Isn’t it a little strange for a cadet that young to become a sibylla?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.63,0:20:29.77,Regular,,0,0,0,,If we aren’t willing to go even that far, we won’t be able to protect the Simoun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.49,0:20:33.79,Regular,,0,0,0,,So that little doll is the only\Nreplacement we’re getting?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.79,0:20:36.74,Regular,,0,0,0,,No, we’ll get one more\Nbefore we leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.74,0:20:38.17,Regular,,0,0,0,,Another special exception?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.17,0:20:40.76,Regular,,0,0,0,,No, she’s normal, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.35,0:20:52.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.85,0:21:00.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,Wow, so that’s a Simoun!\NI’ve never seen the real thing before!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.57,0:21:04.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Aaeru?\NWe’ve been waiting for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.45,0:21:17.84,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Archipelago’s airships are once again violating our borders.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.84,0:21:19.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,We’re going to send out Chor Tempest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.09,0:21:22.33,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don’t think that’s possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.33,0:21:25.02,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m pretty sure Neviril won’t want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.02,0:21:26.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,I think so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.30,0:21:28.55,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.22,0:21:31.31,Regular,,0,0,0,,For that matter,\NParaietta isn’t here, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.31,0:21:33.81,Regular,,0,0,0,,We’re in no condition to fly right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.81,0:21:35.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.98,0:21:39.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,We don’t have anything\Nbut the Simoun to fight with.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.46,0:21:42.94,Regular,,0,0,0,,But would Tempus Spatium forgive us if we did such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.57,0:21:45.36,Regular,,0,0,0,,I can fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.28,0:21:47.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m going!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.03,0:21:50.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,Wait! Sibylla Aaeru!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.03,0:21:53.95,Regular,,0,0,0,,There’s no way she’s a priestess.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.93,0:22:14.62,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s a practice Simile, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.62,0:22:17.02,Regular,,0,0,0,,She can’t perform\NRi Maajons with that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.15,0:22:33.06,Regular,,0,0,0,,You guys can stay behind and pray.\NI came here to fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.00,0:24:06.59,Titles,,85,0,0,,{\blur0.6}Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.59,0:24:12.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Simoun should never\Nhave fallen, but they did.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.51,0:24:17.33,Regular,,0,0,0,,Next time, on Simoun:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.33,0:24:19.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Blue Spring.
